cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is likely to belong to the Natural Language Processing (NLP) sub-category (cs.CL) as it focuses on the use of Variational Autoencoders (VAEs) for modelling text. It could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) and Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories as VAEs are a popular machine learning technique and the paper proposes a fix for a common problem in VAEs. The Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category is also a possibility as the paper discusses the optimization of neural networks. Finally, the Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV) sub-category is a less likely possibility as the paper does not focus on image or video data, but it could still be relevant as VAEs are used in computer vision applications.
